From 4835d97d5c8e84216d49517555d749179ae90001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dhanavandhana Kannan <dhanavan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Jun 2025 12:59:49 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Add hostapd_cli
commands to support TTLM negotiation

Add hostapd_cli support to initiate TTLM request and teardown
action frames from AP MLD.

Add hostapd_cli support to override the response status code of
TTLM to be indicated in association response frames from AP MLD.

Add the below hostapd_cli command to initiate TTLM request for
negotiation of TTLM from AP.

        hostapd_cli -i wlan0 negotiated_ttlm request
        <peer_mld_mac> <dir> <default_link_mapping> <link_mapping_size>
        <num_tids> <TID 0> <Tid_to_link_map> ... <Tid 7> <Tid_to_link_map>
        [<dir> ... <Tid_to_link_map> for another direction]

        Example:

        hostapd_cli -i wlan0 negotiated_ttlm request
        00:03:7f:13:7b:8c dir=0 def_link_map=0 link_map_size=1 num_tids=8 0
        0x1 1 0x1 2 0x1 3 0x1 4 0x1 5 0x1 6 0x1 7 0x1 dir=1 def_link_map=0
        link_map_size=1 num_tids=8 0 0x2 1 0x2 2 0x2 3 0x2 4 0x2 5 0x2 6
        0x2 7 0x2

Add the below command to initiate TTLM teardown for negotiation of
TTLM from AP.

        hostapd_cli -i wlan0 negotiated_ttlm teardown
        <peer_mld_mac>

        Example:

        hostapd_cli -i wlan0 negotiated_ttlm teardown 00:03:7f:13:7b:8c

Add the below command to override TTLM response status code from
previous value.

        hostapd_cli -i wlan0 negotiated_ttlm response <assoc_frame>
        <response_status_code> <peer_mld_mac> <dir> <default_link_mapping>
        <link_mapping_size> <num_tids> <TID 0> <Tid_to_link_map>

        response_status_code = 0 -> success
        response_status_code = 133/134 -> reject/preferred link mapping

        If response code is 134(preferred tid-to-link mapping), then the
        direction and other fields mentioned above should be given.

        If response code is 0/133, then there is no need to give the other
        fields.

        Example:

        hostapd_cli -i wlan0 negotiated_ttlm response assoc_frame=0 134
        00:03:7f:13:7b:8c dir=0 def_link_map=0 link_map_size=1 num_tids=8 0
        0x1 1 0x1 2 0x1 3 0x1 4 0x1 5 0x1 6 0x1 7 0x1 dir=1 def_link_map=0
        link_map_size=1 num_tids=8 0 0x2 1 0x2 2 0x2 3 0x2 4 0x2 5 0x2 6
        0x2 7 0x2

        hostapd_cli -i wlan0 negotiated_ttlm response assoc_frame= 0 133/0

Signed-off-by: Dhanavandhana Kannan <dhanavan@qti.qualcomm.com>
